# Component Hierarchy & Architecture Specification

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This document serves as the technical blueprint for execution by Claude Code.

## 1. Directory Structure Blueprint
```
/src
├── app/
│   ├── layout.tsx         # Root layout with <Canvas> provider
│   ├── page.tsx           # Orchestrator for sections
│   ├── globals.css        # Tailwind directives & custom font loading
│   └── (routes)/          # Future routes if needed
├── components/
│   ├── canvas/            # 3D Scene components
│   │   ├── Scene.tsx      # Main R3F Canvas setup
│   │   ├── Hero.tsx       # Interactive 3D Hero element
│   │   ├── SkillsOrbit.tsx# 3D Skill node system
│   │   └── Projects.tsx   # 3D Carousel logic
│   ├── ui/                # HTML/CSS Overlays
│   │   ├── Overlay.tsx    # Text content container
│   │   ├── Navbar.tsx     # Fixed navigation
│   │   └── Loader.tsx     # 3D loading state
│   └── hooks/             # Custom hooks
│       └── useStore.ts    # Zustand state management
└── lib/                   # Utilities
    └── data.ts            # Static data content
```

## 2. Component Interfaces

### `Scene.tsx`
Wraps the entire 3D experience.
```typescript
interface SceneProps {
  children?: React.ReactNode;
  className?: string; // For positioning
}
// Must include <Canvas> from @react-three/fiber
// Must include <Suspense> for asset loading
```

### `SkillsOrbit.tsx`
Displays skills as orbiting 3D nodes.
```typescript
interface SkillNode {
  name: string;
  category: 'Language' | 'Web' | 'Tool';
  level: number; // 0-100
  color: string; // Hex code
}

// Props
interface SkillsOrbitProps {
  data: SkillNode[];
  radius?: number; // Orbit radius
  speed?: number;  // Rotation speed
}
```

### `Projects.tsx` (Carousel)
Displays projects in a cylindrical or coverflow layout.
```typescript
interface ProjectData {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  techStack: string[];
  imageUrl?: string; // Optional cover image texture
  link?: string;
}

interface ProjectsCarouselProps {
  projects: ProjectData[];
  onSelect?: (project: ProjectData) => void;
}
```

## 3. Data Schema (`lib/data.ts`)
This file should export constant arrays matching the interfaces above.

```typescript
export const SKILLS = [
  { name: 'Java', category: 'Language', level: 90, color: '#0070f3' },
  { name: 'C#', category: 'Language', level: 85, color: '#00BFFF' },
  { name: 'React', category: 'Web', level: 80, color: '#61dafb' },
  // ... others extracted from Resume
];

export const PROJECTS = [
  // Fill with dummy data if exact project details are missing
];
```

## 4. Animation Strategy
- **Entry**: Staggered fade-in for UI elements (`framer-motion`).
- **Scroll**: Parallax effect on 3D camera position (`useScroll` from `@react-three/drei`).
- **Interaction**:
  - `onPointerOver`: Scale up 3D nodes (1.2x).
  - `onClick`: Focus camera on specific section.

